-- Spain Asks EU to Watch Google, Facebook on Tax, Expansion Says
-- B y   M a n u e l   B a i g o r r i
-- 2012-08-16T07:38:52Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-16/spain-asks-eu-to-watch-google-facebook-on-tax-expansion-says.html
The Spanish government asked the
European Union to oversee tax payments in Spain by technology
companies including  Google Inc. (GOOG) ,  Facebook Inc. (FB)  and  Apple Inc. (AAPL) ,
 Expansion  reported, without saying where it got the information.  The Budget Ministry should be getting at least a further 1
billion euros ($1.2 billion) in tax from these companies and is
studying closely their accounting structures, the newspaper
said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Manuel Baigorri in Madrid at 
 mbaigorri@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
